00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:49.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
<i>Homayoun Sakhi</i>: Actually rubab. Yeah. Rubabs. 
<i>Theodore Levin</i>: They also had rubabs in camp.

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:51.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
<i>Homayoun Sakhi</i>: Yeah, uh-huh.

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:58.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
<i>Theodore Levin</i>: And what do you think was the impact of this school in the camp? Did it help raise people's spirits, did it create a sense of cultural identity?

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:07.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
<i>Homayoun Sakhi</i>: Actually that - that school, that was not in - in the camp. That was... we call Tahkal, Tahkal Payan. I was there. That was not in the camp.

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:09.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
<i>Theodore Levin</i>: I see. 
